history.content:
I believe you'll have to enroll in Classics first, then in 61B (the conflict is only allowed from 61B's perspective, AFAIK)

No guarantees about getting off the waitlist for 61B, but typically your chances are good

I was trying to enroll in classics 10b for my phase 2. I got waitlisted (I think the class manually processes waitlists?), and I recently got an email saying I was not moved off the waitlist because my discussion section conflicts with 61b lecture. 

Why isn't 61b allowing the conflict? Is this a glitch in the system? Or do I have to add the breadth first for this to work? I'm a freshman, so I'm pretty unfamiliar with the process.

Thanks!

Edit: Also, if I do have to add the breadth first, am I guaranteed to get off the waitlist for 61b if I drop it and reenroll now?
history.subject: CS61B enrollment conflict with classics 10b
